{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3182884-fb3a-4879-9126-ebbea5032850","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this repo, so here's the general guidance:\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`** — Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test`, not `vstest.console`. Use a script or `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=Cobertura\"\n```\n\n**2. Publish TRX results** (unchanged):\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n```\n\n**3. Publish code coverage**:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n  condition: succeededOrFailed()\n```\n\n### Key differences from `VSTest@3`\n\n| Concern | Old (`VSTest@3`) | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console` | `dotnet test` (built-in) |\n| TRX | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Coverage | `.runsettings` or task param | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Platform filter | Task `platform` input | `--arch` argument |\n\n### NuGet packages needed\n\nEnsure your test projects reference:\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` (or `MSTest` ≥ 3.x which includes it)\n- `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` for the `--collect` collector\n\nWould you like me to create a sample pipeline YAML file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"acb9dbe1-2404-4f21-a7e3-1eb180d8f1d6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository is empty. The user is asking a general knowledge question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":604,"requestId":"67EF:2FF63B:2A2B531:2E78689:69FD34A7"},"id":"228c579f-6692-492c-8e5a-983e30287a9f","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:23.636Z","parentId":"0c75d6f5-bc44-4f4c-aef3-ba4404949ad0"}
